<TD>168</TD>
<TD>Water, Short Beer, Veggies, Shotglass</TD>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER></p><p>I recommend this path for the non-foraging monk brewer.</p><p><OL type=1><LI>Bog Juice<LI>Short Beer<LI>Mead<LI>Short Ale<LI>Fish Wine<LI>Ale<LI> Old Tujim's<LI>Ginesh</OL></p><p><STRONG>Tips</STRONG></p><p><LI>If you are just interested in progressing far enough to make Heady Kiolas, then you can stop after Fish Wine and have a very good success rate. Heady Kiolas themselves are money pits while learning and I never recommend using them to practice your skills up.<LI>You can buy stacks of Snake Scales Spider Legs, Rat Ears, Veggies and Fruits or Fire Beetle Eyes in Newbie Zones such as EC, NRO, North Qeynos or Misty Thicket fairly cheaply.<LI>Kiola Nuts must be bought on Sister Island in the Ocean of Tears.<LI>Fresh Fish can be caught with Fishing skill or bought in many dock area shops.<LI>Barley, Hops, Malt and Yeast must be bought in special brewing areas scattered around Antonica such as in Highhold, Qeynos, Neriak and Freeport. They may be elsewhere but those are all I have found as of yet.<LI>Most other Items can be gotten fairly cheaply in many shops around Norrath.</p>
          </ul>
        </ul>
